│ 16183 /// Merges shuffle masks and emits final shuffle instruction, if required. It                                                                       │
│ 16184 /// supports shuffling of 2 input vectors. It implements lazy shuffles emission,                                                                    │
│ 16185 /// when the actual shuffle instruction is generated only if this is actually                                                                       │
│ 16186 /// required. Otherwise, the shuffle instruction emission is delayed till the                                                                       │
│ 16187 /// end of the process, to reduce the number of emitted instructions and further                                                                    │
│ 16188 /// analysis/transformations.                                                                                                                       │
│ 16189 /// The class also will look through the previously emitted shuffle instructions                                                                    │
│ 16190 /// and properly mark indices in mask as undef.                                                                                                     │
│ 16191 /// For example, given the code                                                                                                                     │
│ 16192 /// \code                                                                                                                                           │
│ 16193 /// %s1 = shufflevector <2 x ty> %0, poison, <1, 0>                                                                                                 │
│ 16194 /// %s2 = shufflevector <2 x ty> %1, poison, <1, 0>                                                                                                 │
│ 16195 /// \endcode                                                                                                                                        │
│ 16196 /// and if need to emit shuffle of %s1 and %s2 with mask <1, 0, 3, 2>, it will                                                                      │
│ 16197 /// look through %s1 and %s2 and emit                                                                                                               │
│ 16198 /// \code                                                                                                                                           │
│ 16199 /// %res = shufflevector <2 x ty> %0, %1, <0, 1, 2, 3>                                                                                              │
│ 16200 /// \endcode                                                                                                                                        │
│ 16201 /// instead.                                                                                                                                        │
│ 16202 /// If 2 operands are of different size, the smallest one will be resized and                                                                       │
│ 16203 /// the mask recalculated properly.                                                                                                                 │
│ 16204 /// For example, given the code                                                                                                                     │
